storical and cultural forces guiding the inner workings of an often misunderstood nation, Ge also teases out many nuances of China's encounter with the contemporary world, using China's past to explain aspects of its present and to provide insight into various paths the nation might follow as the twenty-first century unfolds.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aChinesexAttitudes. 0aNational characteristics, Chinese. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060662140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674985001?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674985001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674985001/original  a978-3-11-060662-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles